data.text:
The only U.S. president born in Nebraska was honored Tuesday on what would have been his 107th birthday.

Two wreaths were laid at the Gerald R. Ford Presidential Museum in Grand Rapids, Michigan. One wreath was from President Trump and the other from the Ford family, according to the Gerald R. Ford Presidential Foundation.

Andrew Gonzalez, volunteer tour guide at the museum and former NTV producer, joined NTV News at Noon to talk about Ford's time in Nebraska and his legacy.

Click the video above to learn about the only president in our nation's history to gain the title without being elected vice president or president.
